history.content: You need to assume you need to attend the sections you sign up for unless the instructor tells you differently.   The answer to this particular question can't be crowd-sourced but has to be directed to the faculty teaching a particular course. It is possible that there will be more concern that you attend the lab you sign up for than the discussion since there are limited lab stations.

Hi, I'm the head TA for CS 61B. You can attend any discussion you would like, and there are no problems with this.

Most of the time, you can attend whatever lab you would like, but in the event of overcrowding, students officially enrolled in the given lab section will be given priority in both workspaces (lab stations) and staff attention. This can (rarely) happen during project deadlines. Thus, I would suggest trying to get into a lab section that works with your schedule.

If none of the currently open sections work with your schedule, I wouldn't sweat the details. Just enroll in something that's open, and you can make arrangements with the TA of the section you would actually regularly attend.
For CS61B, can we attend any discussion/lab, despite what we sign up for?
history.subject: CS61B
